The paper deals with motion planning for quadrotors, which is a robotics problem, and specifically addresses the issue of stochasticity in the environment. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses multiobjective optimization and GPU acceleration, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of particle-based approximation, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV).
